# Self-Service General Dashboards

This Notebook provides access to General Dashboards and tile/variable examples. Scroll down for a detailed description of the Dashboard, Use Cases, Install Instructions and much more. You can download/upload any content and use the dashboard as is. Or you can take certain portions of the dashboard, remove/add content to fit your specific use case. If you are interested in building your own content from scratch within your wireframe, listed below are a few tile and variable examples to get you started.

## Service Overview Dashboard
This dashboard provides an overview for your Services focused on Response Time, Requests, Failure Rates and CPU Time.
 
![](data:image/webp;base64,)

### Prerequisites

None.

### Target Audience

- SRE
- Developer

### Use Cases

- Are my Services performing as expected?
- Are errors impacting my Services?
- Are performance and error trends impacting my Services?
- What days/times are my Services performing best?
- Is my Service traffic trending in the right direction?
- 
### Install Instructions

- Click [Dashboard JSON](https://github.com/TechShady/Dynatrace-Dashboards-Gen3/blob/main/Service%20Overview.json) and select Download raw file ![](data:image/webp;base64,)
- Launch the Dashboard app
- Select Upload and select the JSON file for your download folder
- Select Review all code in the upper right hand corner of your Dashboard
- Check Always trust code in this document and then select Accept and run
- Test out you Dashboard by selecting options from the Variable dropdown list and adjusting the Dashboard timeframe

## Host Overview Dashboard

This dashboard provides an overview for your Hosts focused on CPU and Memory consumption by Cloud Types.
 
![](data:image/webp;base64,)

### Prerequisites

None.

### Target Audience

- SRE
- Developer
- Infrastructure Manager 

### Use Cases

- Are my Hosts performing as expected?
- How much Memory is my Host consuming?
- What is my Host CPU consumption??
- What days/times are my Hosts consuming the most Memory/CPU?
- What Cloud Type is consuming the most Memory/CPU?
- What is the Memory/CPU consumption trend for my Hosts running in a certain Cloud Type?

### Install Instructions

- Click [Dashboard JSON](https://github.com/TechShady/Dynatrace-Dashboards-Gen3/blob/main/Host%20Overview.json) and select Download raw file ![](data:image/webp;base64,)
- Launch the Dashboard app
- Select Upload and select the JSON file for your download folder
- Select Review all code in the upper right hand corner of your Dashboard
- Check Always trust code in this document and then select Accept and run
- Test out you Dashboard by selecting options from the Variable dropdown list and adjusting the Dashboard timeframe
